The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Steps to revive film societies
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       Steps to revive film societies
          A STAFF REPORTER                              
	Chief minister Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee on Tuesday asked Calcutta Film Society to submit a report on what the state should do to create the right infrastructure and environment to promote good film culture. He also asked for a report on how the Federation of Film Societies of India (FFSI) and film societies across the country could collaborate with Nandan and Cinema Shotobarsho Bhaban, which houses a film library and archive. These two steps may give a fresh lease of life to the film societies., Bhattacharjee said at the inauguration of the golden jubilee celebration of FFSI, the apex body of all film societies, at Nandan.        
	nFour persons were arrested late on Monday from an apartment in Baguiati allegedly for running a sleaze racket. Police said Surajit Ghosh, 34, and Nandini Ghosh, 30, were running the racket for over six months. The other two held were Rajib Mukherjee, 32, an engineer from Dum Dum, and Tapasi Dey. The four have been sent to judicial custody for 14 days.        
	nThe Calcutta Municipal Corporation for the first time on Tuesday started issuing photo identity cards to its 37,000-odd employees.        
	nAn exhibition titled Know Your Army will be held on January 10 and 11 at Fort William. The exhibition will be open for all between 10am and 4pm on both the days.        
	nResidents blocked the Bidhan Sarani-Raja Naba Krishna Street crossing for an hour on Tuesday demanding the arrest of the man who allegedly drove Raja Das to suicide. They said Das hanged himself after being slapped by his girlfriends uncle Ram Prasad Rajak.                                                                                                                                                                         
